      "span_text": "KLKB1 (kallikrein B) is also a plasma protein secreted by the liver. It can stimulate release of neutrophil elastase release during blood coagulation, and also participates in production of plasmin from plasminogen, the kallikreinkinin system, the renin-angiotensin system and the alternative complement pathway [CITATION_5] ."
